FBIS4-56581 "drlat088_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 Barbados Haiti Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Killed 4 May Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Killed 4 May FL0505194994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 5 May 94 FL0505194994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] We have learned from a reliable source that Jean-Verdy Bastien, owner of the Celeste Borlette Banks and the private radio station Celeste FM, was assassinated on the night of 4 May at about 2200 in upper Delmas. His driver was also injured during the attack against him by a group of armed men who had set up an ambush. According to our source, Jean-Verdy Bastien's body was transported to the general hospital morgue.
